Russell Brand introduces his guest-edited issue of the New Statesman

From climate change and gay rights to transcendental meditation and dealing with drug abuse, this special issue of the magazine explores the theme of REVOLUTION.

This week, Russell Brand has guest-edited the New Statesman. His issue is themed around the idea of REVOLUTION, and includes contributions from David Lynch, Noel Gallagher, Naomi Klein, Amanda Palmer, Alec Baldwin, Gary Lineker, Graham Hancock and many more, as well as cover art by Shepard Fairey. More details at newstatesman.com/russellbrand
